modules.description: Provides string manipulation functions including case conversion, substring extraction, and pattern matching. Operates on OCaml's native string type and regular expressions. Enables efficient text processing for tasks like log parsing and data validation.

Registers custom syntax specifiers for expressions, patterns, and when clauses in OCaml code, enabling extension of literal syntax during parsing. Operates on custom linked list structures (`llist`) and OCaml AST nodes, supporting traversal, transformation, and conversion to standard lists. Provides utilities for handling escaped string data and constructing AST nodes from structured data.
